rComments: WORST TEACHER EVER AVOID AT ALL COST

Clearly knowledgable but lacks the ability to teach. Oppressive/rude and unnecessarily calls out students. Dismisses questions during class. Lec/DGDS are mandatory as attendance is taken and each DGD has a quiz/worksheet worth marks. Avoid taking the class with this Prof if you can. Eventually people stopped laughing at her jokes out of fear.

She is very intelligent and very helpful one on one but everything kind of goes downhill during class lectures and DGDs. When answering questions from students she often responds  in a way that comes off as condescending which I don't think is her intention but regardless it makes going to this class a lot more difficult.

Prof Brebner is very knowledgeable and evidently has a passion for English writing/grammar.  She does, however, have some difficulty with personal interactions, often comes across as short, insensitive or rude. As a result the class atmosphere is oppressive and student are afraid to speak up. This atmosphere is not conducive to learning.

She's a very well organized prof but she's also one of the most passive aggressive and downright rude prof I have ever had. Her DGD are basically another lecture and there's quizzes once a week and class attendance is mandatory, so thats fun. Don't take this class if you can help.

Knows the content very well but comes off as snobby and rude. Cuts students off and is often less than helpful when answering questions. Be careful when arguing anything,she will most likely shoot you down. Never, ever call her anything other then Professor Brebner. She has an issue with the title "Mrs"... Don't take this class if you can avoid it.

So nervous she comes off as rude and very harsh towards students. One-on-one she's fine and helpful, but I dread going to class. Everyone is dead quiet and a bit scared of her. Quick to tell students they shouldn't be there and should just leave. Makes her students feel stupid and shy to speak up during class.
